-- в”Ђв”Ђ Windsurf в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$AI-powered coding editor built around the Cascade agent for multi-file code generation and debugging, formerly known as Codeium, now integrated into Cognition after its 2025 acquisition.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free plan available; Pro from USD15 per user per month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2021, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Approximately 250 employees at the time of its 2025 acquisition by Cognition$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Mountain View, California, US$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Windsurf Review 2026: AI Code Editor Features, Pricing, and the Cognition Acquisition$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Learn what Windsurf (formerly Codeium) offers as an agentic AI code editor, its Cascade agent, pricing plans, and its 2025 acquisition by Cognition.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Windsurf is an AI-powered code editor built by a company originally founded in 2021 as Codeium, headquartered in Mountain View, California. Codeium initially built an AI code-completion product before launching the Windsurf Editor in November 2024, describing it as one of the first fully agentic IDEs; the company completed its rebrand from Codeium to Windsurf in April 2025. The product's core feature is Cascade, an AI agent that maintains deep contextual awareness of a codebase to make coordinated multi-file edits, run terminal commands, proactively debug issues, and generate code from natural-language instructions, distinguishing it from simpler autocomplete-only assistants. Windsurf is available as a standalone editor and as plugins for VS Code and JetBrains IDEs, supporting a wide range of programming languages. In 2025 the company went through significant upheaval: Google hired away Windsurf's CEO Varun Mohan, co-founder Douglas Chen, and key research leaders in a reported 2.4 billion dollar reverse-acquihire, leaving much of the roughly 250-person team behind without its founding leadership. Within days, Cognition, the company behind the autonomous coding agent Devin, signed a deal to acquire the remaining Windsurf business for approximately 250 million dollars, with all remaining Windsurf employees participating financially in the deal and having vesting cliffs waived. Since the acquisition, Cognition has continued developing the Windsurf editor while working to integrate its intellectual property into Cognition's broader product line. More recently, Cognition rebranded the Windsurf editor as Devin Desktop, introducing an Agent Client Protocol that allows multiple coding agents, including Codex, Claude Agent, and Devin itself, to run within the same interface, positioning the product as a general cockpit for AI coding agents rather than a single-vendor assistant. Historically, Windsurf's pricing included a Free plan with limited agentic actions, a Pro plan at 15 dollars per user per month, a Teams plan at 30 dollars per user per month, and an Enterprise plan at 60 dollars per user per month, with paid tiers unlocking more premium model credits, higher usage limits, and admin and security controls for organizations. Prospective users and existing customers should be aware that the product and its branding are actively evolving following the acquisition, and the windsurf.com domain now points to Cognition's Devin Desktop product pages.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '758d739b-574e-4253-96df-178cefd5f067';

