-- в”Ђв”Ђ WinterCMS в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Free, open-source content management system built on Laravel, forked from October CMS in 2021 to remain community-driven and free for good.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$open-source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2021, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$WinterCMS Review 2026: Open-Source Laravel CMS Features and Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$See what WinterCMS offers as a free, open-source Laravel-based CMS forked from October CMS, including features, pricing, and pros and cons.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$WinterCMS, usually styled Winter CMS, is a free and open-source content management system built on the Laravel PHP framework. It was created in March 2021 when a group of core maintainers forked the codebase of October CMS after a breakdown in communication with October's founders, who subsequently made October CMS a paid, proprietary product. The Winter CMS team explicitly positioned their fork as a commitment to keeping the platform free, open source, and community-driven going forward, in contrast to October's shift toward a closed, commercial model. The project is stewarded by Frostbyte Foundation Inc and developed by a team of specialist and agency-based developers rather than a single commercial vendor. Functionally, WinterCMS emphasizes four core strengths: speed, through a smart, performance-focused system design; simplicity, allowing developers to build complex sites primarily with standard HTML, CSS, and JavaScript rather than proprietary templating concepts; stability, through backwards-compatible updates intended to protect long-term site investments; and security, through full source code transparency and prompt handling of reported issues. The platform includes a plugin and theme architecture along with a marketplace for extending core functionality, letting developers add e-commerce, forms, blogs, and other capabilities without building everything from scratch. Because it is built on Laravel, WinterCMS benefits from Laravel's mature ecosystem, tooling, and conventions, which makes it approachable for PHP developers already familiar with that framework. WinterCMS is released under the MIT license, meaning there is no cost to use, modify, or redistribute the core software, and there is no vendor lock-in tied to a commercial company. It is aimed at designers, developers, and agencies of varying experience levels, supporting projects ranging from small brochure websites to larger, more complex applications and e-commerce sites. Because it is self-hosted and open source, users are responsible for their own hosting, and there is no official managed hosting or SaaS tier offered directly by the WinterCMS project, distinguishing it from commercial hosted CMS platforms like WordPress.com, Wix, or Webflow. The most recent tracked release at research time was v1.2.12. WinterCMS competes primarily with other open-source, self-hosted CMS platforms, positioning its Laravel foundation, backwards compatibility guarantees, and community governance model as its main differentiators.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'b894fce3-7970-4562-8f82-502c745c7472';

